. Our analysis indicates that the\ncontribution of the $3N$ force in the $t$ matrix is small for the differential\ncross section and it is sizable for the spin observables, in particular, for\nthe analyzing power. A chiral expansion order-by-order analysis of the\nscattering observables confirms the convergence of our results at the\nnext-to-next-to-next-to-leading-order, as already established in our previous\nwork.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 Oct 2020 20:29:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-10"}
